+<a id="json-reporter-format"></a>
+## JSON reporter output format
+
+The JSON reporter (`--reporter json`) produces output that complies with
+[RFC 8259](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8259).
+
+### String escaping
+
+All string values in the JSON output (test names, section names, assertion
+expressions, captured output, etc.) are escaped according to RFC 8259 §7:
+
+* The six named sequences are used where applicable:
+  `\"`, `\\`, `\b`, `\f`, `\n`, `\r`, `\t`
+* All other Unicode control characters in the range U+0000–U+001F that do
+  not have a named sequence (for example U+0001 SOH, U+000B VT) are
+  represented as `\uXXXX` four-hex-digit escape sequences.
+
+This means the JSON output is always valid regardless of what characters
+appear in test names or captured output.
+
+
